      "description": "This 2002 Carrera features the refined 3.6L flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. The G96 six-speed manual transaxle offers precise gate engagement, delivering power to the rear wheels with classic 911 weight bias. The chassis remains composed with a multi-link rear suspension geometry and staggered alloys, while braking is handled by four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers for exceptional thermal capacity. Critically, this M96 engine has been serviced with an IMS bearing retrofit and a new rear main seal, addressing common failure points. A mechanically sound, driver-focused example with excellent hydraulic steering feedback and a high power-to-weight ratio.",
